description: {"blocks":[{"key":"3i4rr","text":"This protocol collection explains how to build a low-cost, lightweight system to implant Neuropixels 1.0 probes into mice, record during freely moving behavior, then recover the probe for future use. This protocol explains how to recover a previously implanted probe and clean for future use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"eh4eh","text":"Tools:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":5}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8ciht","text":"Dovetail holder \u0026 stereotax adapter (Sensapex uMp-NH \u0026 uMp-NPR-200)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2u743","text":"Tiny flathead screwdriver (Wiha, 0.8 x 40)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1nk9q","text":"Scissors","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ejesu","text":"Headbar stereotactic adapters (see Implant surgery protocol)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":35,"length":16}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ekg0d","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a93rq","text":"Consumables:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":12}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e9gc8","text":"Isoflurane","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fhf76","text":"Tergazyme (1g per 100mL, Alconox 1325, made within 8h of surgery)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bqv1u","text":"dH20","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8al5f","text":"Set the nosecone to the position you recorded from the implant surgery. Attach mouse to headbar stereotactic adapters.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dfj5d","text":"Remove all the tape to expose the screws and probe.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5lo19","text":"Attach the Sensapex holder and set the stereotax to the angle used in the implant surgery. Tax to the dovetail cap. A fully open Sensapex holder can be taxed in from anterior or dorsal to the dovetail holder.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6tjml","text":"Adjust the screws so the holder grips the dovetail cap.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"v0bh","text":"Unscrew the wings from the body. Screws can be saved for future surgeries.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"db3e9","text":"Slowly tax up to bring the probe \u0026 body piece away from the animal. Set back to 0 degrees and adjust the arm so the probe is away from the surgical field.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"af4qf","text":"Lower the probe into tergazyme and let sit for 30 minutes, then rinse with dH2O.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4tupg","text":"Remove the mouse from the stereotax and prepare for perfusion.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cbva1","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"c034o","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"965F1FD0936111EC99715FC4A1DBE38E","height":177.890909090909,"id":309253,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"cpb6h","text":"Remaining implant after probe is explanted. After perfusion, the assembly can be removed from the skull in 1 piece by grasping the headbar and rotating it away from the skull.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","original_name":"image.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jqahbqrq7.jpg","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jqafbqrq7.jpg","type":1,"webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jqagbqrq7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jqaebqrq7.webp","width":305.74999999999983}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"25v4f","text":"Set O2 flow rate to 1-1.5L/min and isoflurane to 3%. Place mouse in anesthetic chamber.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"deaes","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9e8b2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"safety","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"c1j3e","text":"Use vacuum systems connected to isoflurane lines and work on a downdraft table to move uninhaled isoflurane away from the surgeon.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cd623","text":"When breathing has slowed to 1Hz, move animal to the toothbar. Switch isoflurane from chamber to nosecone. Wait until unresponsive to pedal reflex test, then lower to 1.5% isoflurane.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"afqpa","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"a87km","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9jila","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"71iuv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"avttg","text":"Monitor and record anesthetic depth throughout procedure. Ears and toes should be pink, respiration should be once per 1-2 seconds, and pedal reflex should be lost. If respiration slows or extremities start to lose color, lower isoflurane levels. If respiration speeds up or reflex is present, increase isoflurane levels and halt the procedure until animal is fully anesthetized again.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"auj7h","text":"Assemble following the Assembly protocol, skipping the steps that modify the probe (sharpening, soldering wire to the PCB, attaching the body piece). Extend the ground wire back to full length and attach a new pin.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":23,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
